1
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:07,540
=Live and Love S2=
=Special Event=

2
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:09,720
(Live and Love Special Event)
Welcome to Balance Island.

3
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:12,200
It's time for the islanders' game.

4
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:14,280
(Boys' Dorm; Balance Zone; Dining Room;
Water Arena) This round is a partner match.

5
00:00:14,280 --> 00:00:15,080
Male and female islanders

6
00:00:15,080 --> 00:00:18,240
will form five mixed-gender pairs

7
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:20,520
based on the previous pairings.

8
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:22,000
The ultimate winners

9
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,960
will receive a Romantic Pack.

10
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:24,520
(Last round's captain)
How should we pair up?

11
00:00:24,520 --> 00:00:25,160
Alright.

12
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:26,560
I'll team up with Enda.

13
00:00:26,580 --> 00:00:27,580
(Yang Tinghong, Zhao Enda)

14
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:29,440
(Wu Yihan, Yang Tianyu)
Tianyu with Han.

15
00:00:29,520 --> 00:00:30,480
Guanjie with Yan.

16
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:31,760
(Zhu Huiyan, Wu Guanjie)

17
00:00:31,760 --> 00:00:32,240
I'll go with Yijia.

18
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:32,800
Yijia?

19
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,320
Sure.

20
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:34,280
(Chen Yijia, Huang Jiawei
Bestie Duo)

21
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,520
I'll with Lu.

22
00:00:35,520 --> 00:00:36,240
Bro!

23
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,420
(Ding Wanning, Lu Yanting) (Bros Duo)
Bro!

24
00:00:39,440 --> 00:00:40,320
Folding clothes.

25
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,920
Seriously?

26
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:42,880
No way.

27
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:44,640
I'm good at folding,

28
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:45,400
but not dressing.

29
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:47,440
(Just smile)
Now, for the game rules.

30
00:00:47,440 --> 00:00:49,800
This round is "Sweet Burden."

31
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,240
Islanders will compete in pairs.

32
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,880
("Sweet Burden" Game Rules:)
Each pair competes in one heat.

33
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:56,920
The male islander must carry
the female islander on his back,

34
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,480
while she tries to dress him

35
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:00,920
in as many clothes as possible.

36
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:02,400
There is a three-minute limit.

37
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,600
Successfully putting on
a T-shirt earns one point.

38
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,280
Successfully putting on

39
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:08,440
and buttoning a seven-button
shirt earns five points.

40
00:01:08,440 --> 00:01:09,920
The top two scoring pairs

41
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,760
will move on to the next round.

42
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,880
Can I carry him?

43
00:01:12,940 --> 00:01:14,020
(Wait, what?)

44
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:16,720
Sure.

45
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,760
If you get tired,

46
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:18,800
Lu can carry you instead.

47
00:01:18,860 --> 00:01:19,700
(That's wild.)

48
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:21,600
(Don't be so mean!)

49
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:22,920
(Sorry, bro.)
I'm sorry about this,

50
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:23,360
Lu.

51
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:24,760
(Don't underestimate me.)
I'm 76 kg.

52
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,120
I'm 55 kg.

53
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,120
You think that'll work?

54
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,620
(Yes? No?)

55
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,860
(I think I...)

56
00:01:30,940 --> 00:01:31,440
(I got this. Trust me.)

57
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:32,320
(I trust you.)
You got this!

58
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:32,680
You got this,

59
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:33,320
bro.

60
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,300
(Can't lose.)
We gotta win.

61
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:35,240
(Have mercy)
Again?

62
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:35,880
We...

63
00:01:36,240 --> 00:01:36,800
We gotta win.

64
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:37,880
(What's wrong?)
We're too competitive.

65
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:38,760
That's not good.

66
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:39,360
(Keep it cool.)

67
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:40,320
(Competitive)
Not good?

68
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,280
(Be humble)
Time for a change.

69
00:01:41,820 --> 00:01:42,980
(Helpless sigh)

70
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:44,680
Grab a shirt.

71
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:45,600
(Strategizing)
A shirt?

72
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,160
I'll lean forward.

73
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:46,920
I'll carry you.

74
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:48,560
Yeah, I'll help you with the sleeves.

75
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:49,900
You wanna button it?

76
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:50,990
(The crucial part)
Gotta button it right.

77
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:51,680
Of course.

78
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:52,280
(Leave it to me.)

79
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,200
I've got this.

80
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:55,120
Which one gets us more points?

81
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,680
Definitely the shirt.

82
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,080
Okay.

83
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:00,660
(Shirt, too)

84
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,320
Put on as many shirts as possible?

85
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:04,700
(Shirt or T-shirt?)

86
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:05,960
I think this strategy

87
00:02:05,960 --> 00:02:06,800
is a bit tricky.

88
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,880
(Shirt, too.)
Honestly, shirts are the way to go.

89
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,280
Yang's got the advantage.

90
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,720
She's light.

91
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,560
She's light too.

92
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:15,900
(Take the hint.)
I know.

93
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,260
(Rock-paper-scissors to decide the order.)

94
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,600
Guys first.

95
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,000
Up go up,

96
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,400
down go down.

97
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,160
Odd one out goes first.

98
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:25,680
Odd side up.

99
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:27,440
Black, white,

100
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:27,880
go.

101
00:02:28,140 --> 00:02:29,320
(Black, white, white, black, black.)

102
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:29,760
Us two.

103
00:02:30,320 --> 00:02:31,680
Losers go first.

104
00:02:31,680 --> 00:02:32,200
Alright.

105
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,120
Rock, paper, scissors.

106
00:02:33,180 --> 00:02:34,080
(Tie)
(Paper, paper.)

107
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,680
Rock, paper, scissors.

108
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:36,620
(Win)
(Paper, rock.)

109
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:37,400
We're up first.

110
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:40,580
(First pair on stage)

111
00:02:43,740 --> 00:02:44,740
(Three-minute countdown starts.)

112
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:47,540
(Prioritizing the shirt)

113
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:48,360
He's got the right idea.

114
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:49,960
I'll do the same.

115
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,000
They're being too greedy.

116
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:56,600
We'll see.

117
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,200
(Watching)
If the shirts aren't tricky...

118
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:59,600
That's a lot of buttons.

119
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,100
(Struggling with the sleeve)

120
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:03,020
(Got it on.)

121
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:04,980
(Losing balance. She's sliding.)

122
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:08,580
(You good, bro?)

123
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:09,520
Can you carry me?

124
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:10,180
(Worried)

125
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:10,800
I can.

126
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,800
(No problem)
Piece of cake.

127
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,560
It'll just be a bit tiring.

128
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:14,680
Tiring, you said?

129
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:16,560
(Why tiring now?)
Holding it for three minutes is exhausting.

130
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,680
I'm the lightest girl here.

131
00:03:19,110 --> 00:03:20,080
(That helps.)
I've got this.

132
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,080
Don't worry.

133
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:22,700
(Alright then)

134
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:24,380
You okay?

135
00:03:24,380 --> 00:03:25,320
(Starting to button up)
This button..

136
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:26,200
Hold on.

137
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,600
This one's tricky.

138
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,400
(Stuck)
It's fine.

139
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,080
- You got this.
- My hands.

140
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,680
Not a single button's done yet.

141
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,040
I want him to do it himself.

142
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:34,760
Can I do it?

143
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:35,780
(Volunteering)

144
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,360
The guys can't button themselves, right?

145
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:38,620
(No)

146
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:39,760
Arms long enough?

147
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:40,560
Can you reach the buttons?

148
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:41,800
Give it a shot.

149
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,000
Your chest is too broad.

150
00:03:44,340 --> 00:03:45,980
(What kind of excuse is that?)

151
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:48,140
(Heh-heh)

152
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:49,880
Good, one button done.

153
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:51,480
(One's done)
I'm despairing.

154
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:53,560
I'm losing it.

155
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,880
I wish I hadn't gotten my nails done.

156
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,040
(Buttoning is a pain.)
It's so hard to button.

157
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,520
We could finish the shirt first,

158
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,320
then check the time.

159
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,760
With 30 seconds left,

160
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:03,520
(Forming a plan)

161
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,920
we can finish two shirts

162
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,200
and a few T-shirts.

163
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:06,880
Okay.

164
00:04:07,860 --> 00:04:09,420
(Still wrestling with buttons)

165
00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:13,180
(Found a rhythm)

166
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,760
Wait, let me count.

167
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,360
One, two...

168
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:17,800
Just button this up.

169
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,160
No more holes left.

170
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:20,440
At the top.

171
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:26,320
I won't reach seven at this rate.

172
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,720
(Don't worry.)
Keep buttoning.

173
00:04:28,280 --> 00:04:29,160
I can't do it.

174
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,140
(Frustrated)

175
00:04:30,140 --> 00:04:32,100
(Exhausted)

176
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:32,680
Hurry.

177
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,440
This one.

178
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,120
Where's the buttonhole?

179
00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:37,740
(Helpless)

180
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,280
So stylish. I love it.

181
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:41,640
Done.

182
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:42,360
One more T-shirt,

183
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:42,720
okay?

184
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:43,400
Sure.

185
00:04:44,740 --> 00:04:46,220
(Pushed to the limit)

186
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:47,320
The village chief's worn out.

187
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,520
His back's practically broken.

188
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,460
(Back-breaking work)

189
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:54,900
(Second piece: T-shirt)

190
00:04:54,980 --> 00:04:56,440
(Hang in there, bro)

191
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,960
Alright, you've got this.

192
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:58,280
Here.

193
00:04:58,280 --> 00:04:59,880
One more T-shirt.

194
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:00,440
One more?

195
00:05:00,860 --> 00:05:03,620
(Shaking)

196
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:04,960
Hurry up!

197
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:05,640
On it.

198
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,000
Go.

199
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,000
Okay.

200
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:08,360
Alright.

201
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:12,080
One more.

202
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:15,020
(10 seconds left.)

203
00:05:18,980 --> 00:05:21,540
(Bite down and bear it.)

204
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,800
That's enough.

205
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,160
Done.

206
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,020
(Time's up.)

207
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:27,400
(Pushing the limit)

208
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,920
Careful.

209
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:30,760
Get up.

210
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:31,640
Thanks.

211
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,100
(Completely out of breath)

212
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,120
That was great.

213
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:37,700
(Good job.)

214
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:39,000
(Scoring the first group)
Three pieces.

215
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,680
Three T-shirts.

216
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:40,900
(1 T-shirt: 1 point)

217
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:43,440
That undershirt is pretty stylish.

218
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:46,340
(2 T-shirts: 2 points)

219
00:05:46,340 --> 00:05:47,340
(3 T-shirts: 3 points)
Yes, seven buttons.

220
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:48,900
(Trendy outfit)

221
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:53,220
(Huang Jiawei & Chen Yijia: 3 T-shirts
and 1 shirt, 8 points, currently 1st place)

222
00:05:54,740 --> 00:05:55,700
(That was so hard.)

223
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:56,480
Impressive.

224
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:57,640
Eight points.

225
00:05:58,280 --> 00:05:58,880
Eight points.

226
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,320
Nice job.

227
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,600
Impressive.

228
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,880
Awesome. They set the bar high.

229
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:06,000
Rock-paper-scissors?

230
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,560
Let's do it.

231
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,520
Rock, paper,

232
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,600
scissors!

233
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,940
(Lose)
(Scissors, rock, rock.)

234
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:13,720
I'm going.

235
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:17,780
(Second pair on stage)

236
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:20,840
Jump.

237
00:06:23,780 --> 00:06:25,300
(Perfect form)

238
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
(Way to go, bro.)
So steady, Guanjie.

239
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,440
They both went for shirts.

240
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:34,500
(Sitting up straight.)

241
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:35,240
Impressive.

242
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:36,600
Yeah.

243
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:37,460
Like riding a horse.

244
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,360
This is awesome.

245
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,680
See?

246
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,360
Now his upper body is totally free.

247
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,480
Button it up.

248
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,200
Awesome, Guanjie.

249
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,140
(Impressed)

250
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:53,860
(Pulling it together)

251
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:56,500
(Relaxed)

252
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,120
Guanjie looks so chill.

253
00:06:58,140 --> 00:06:59,220
(Agree)

254
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:00,520
He's completely still.

255
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:01,920
Perfect horse stance.

256
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:03,700
(Classic horse stance)

257
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:05,700
(Struggling with the buttons)

258
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,600
No rush.

259
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:07,280
(Reassuring)
No rush.

260
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:10,480
These buttons-

261
00:07:10,540 --> 00:07:11,280
(Such a hassle)

262
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:12,120
They're too small.

263
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:12,720
How many now?

264
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,080
Count them.

265
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:14,960
One.

266
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,580
(Counting the buttons)

267
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,160
Two. Three. Four.

268
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:20,720
Come on.

269
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,320
Do up another one.

270
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:22,920
Wrong buttonhole.

271
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:25,280
Don't rush.

272
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,120
Focus.

273
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:26,760
Get it on.

274
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:27,640
One more piece.

275
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,680
Another shirt?

276
00:07:29,280 --> 00:07:29,880
Do T-shirts.

277
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:30,720
This one.

278
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,480
Is it all buttoned?

279
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,320
Not yet.

280
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,040
Haven't finished?

281
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,160
They'll get zero points otherwise.

282
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,240
Better to button it up.

283
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:36,640
Yeah.

284
00:07:38,420 --> 00:07:39,780
(Grabbed another T-shirt.)

285
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,040
Here, take this one.

286
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:42,840
(Sticking with the shirts)

287
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:43,600
Okay.

288
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,280
Another shirt? Still?

289
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,040
Seriously?

290
00:07:47,860 --> 00:07:50,620
(30 seconds left)

291
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,200
Not enough time.

292
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:52,720
Shirts first,

293
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,520
then T-shirts.

294
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,880
(Giving up on the shirts)
Let's skip shirts.

295
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:56,960
But T-shirts alone won't

296
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:57,920
get you to eight points.

297
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,520
We can do it.

298
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,120
Yeah, we can.

299
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:00,440
Yes,

300
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,040
(Confident)
we can.

301
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:01,840
We can handle it.

302
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:02,800
We've got this.

303
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,040
Hopefully.

304
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,120
Now we're talking.

305
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,760
(Spoke too soon.)
What if we get zero?

306
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:07,680
It should work out.

307
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,080
It will.

308
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:08,400
And

309
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,480
we don't need to be first.

310
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,200
Just as long as we're not last.

311
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:12,200
Right.

312
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:12,600
Right?

313
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:15,340
(10 seconds left)

314
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:22,100
(Time's up.)

315
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:22,880
No way.

316
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,160
Can't button that many.

317
00:08:24,260 --> 00:08:25,580
(Scoring the second group)

318
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,320
Not even close.

319
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:27,420
(One button)

320
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:28,180
(Two buttons)

321
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:29,580
(First shirt: two buttons)

322
00:08:32,140 --> 00:08:33,280
(2 shirts, neither has 7 buttons.)
One short.

323
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:33,800
One short.

324
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:36,780
(Wu Guanjie & Zhu Huiyan: 0 T-shirt,
0 shirts, 0 points, currently 2nd place)

325
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,000
I told you

326
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,680
not to go for so many shirts.

327
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:43,100
(In disbelief)

328
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:43,800
Zero?

329
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:44,320
Zero points.

330
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,360
No points if we didn't get all seven?

331
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,560
Yes, it must be exactly seven.

332
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,440
Yang, you're up.

333
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:49,880
Our turn?

334
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:50,320
Our turn now?

335
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:56,660
(Third group)

336
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,960
If shirts are hard, go with T-shirts.

337
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,920
(Worried)
Okay, try buttoning one.

338
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:01,520
It's okay.

339
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:02,200
I can do it.

340
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:05,540
(Round 3 begins)

341
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:07,320
Let's do shirts.

342
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:07,680
Right.

343
00:09:09,860 --> 00:09:11,980
(Opening strike)

344
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,400
You're steady, very steady.

345
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,240
(Teammate's approval)

346
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,360
Unstoppably steady.

347
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:18,560
Left arm? Right arm?

348
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,720
Yeah, just like that.

349
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:20,840
It's reversed.

350
00:09:21,020 --> 00:09:22,340
(Noticed first)

351
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:24,320
Over here.

352
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,420
(Shirt's on)

353
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,640
Hard for them.

354
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:29,760
(Experienced advice)
Enda's too tall.

355
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,480
You count.

356
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:32,280
Okay.

357
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,420
(You count. I button)

358
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,650
(Clear division of labor)
One.

359
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:36,320
No rush.

360
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:36,960
Two buttons.

361
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:39,400
Am I heavy?

362
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:39,880
Not at all.

363
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:42,600
Three.

364
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,380
(Super smooth.)

365
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:45,120
Four.

366
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:46,720
Five.

367
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,400
They're like two turtles,

368
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,760
drifting steadily on the sea.

369
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,440
Six.

370
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:58,480
Seven.

371
00:09:58,880 --> 00:09:59,680
(First shirt done.)
Next shirt.

372
00:09:59,820 --> 00:10:00,980
(Choosing another high-score shirt)

373
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,080
Sleeve won't go in.

374
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,460
(Getting tougher)

375
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:10,760
Just finish this button.

376
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:14,540
(90 seconds left)

377
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:15,080
One.

378
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,000
Two.

379
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:20,440
So fast.

380
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,660
(Unbelievably smooth)

381
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:22,920
Stand up a little.

382
00:10:22,920 --> 00:10:23,560
Three.

383
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,560
I'll stand straighter.

384
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,400
(Changing stance)
Hold my legs.

385
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:28,000
How many?

386
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:28,480
Four.

387
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,120
No problem. Continue.

388
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,000
Look at his head.

389
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,440
(Got inspired)
Keep your head down.

390
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,760
I'll slip it over you.

391
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,480
I'll do this.

392
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,410
(Strategizing)
Yeah.

393
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,680
We're taking this seriously.

394
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:38,800
Better stop it.

395
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,340
(Filled with competitive drive)

396
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:42,780
(Time's almost up)
Just go for it.

397
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,000
(60 seconds left)
All in, right?

398
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:44,520
Right.

399
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:46,520
How many now?

400
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,120
Might need two more buttons.

401
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,080
Two more?

402
00:10:50,020 --> 00:10:51,420
(Proficient)

403
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:51,960
(Fast)

404
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,040
There's one at the top.

405
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,520
(Working smoothly)
You can do the top one.

406
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:56,960
Okay?

407
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:57,480
Can you?

408
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,240
It's fine.

409
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:00,920
Done.

410
00:11:00,920 --> 00:11:02,160
(Second shirt finished)
Great, next one.

411
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:03,300
(Picks a T-shirt)

412
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:05,840
How much time left?

413
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:10,660
(Sliding down again)

414
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:11,800
Keep going.

415
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,300
(Unfazed)

416
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,240
Maybe we just go with the T-shirts.

417
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,260
(Prefers the simpler T-shirt)

418
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:18,780
That works too.

419
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:19,700
(Agrees)

420
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,000
Yeah, that's the move.

421
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,840
I'll lean forward,
and you slip it over my head.

422
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,040
Then over my arms.

423
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:27,940
(This tactic sounds familiar.)

424
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:28,720
Remember,

425
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:30,160
keep your head down.

426
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,400
I'll pull it over you.

427
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,240
And my hands like this.

428
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:33,720
Right.

429
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:36,220
(Totally in sync now)

430
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,880
Let's do rock-paper-scissors with them.

431
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:39,360
(Can't wait)
What if they want to go first?

432
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,080
You go.

433
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:40,520
(You go?)

434
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:41,160
(You go!)
No, you go.

435
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,240
You guys should do it.

436
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,940
(Then I'll do it!)

437
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:45,440
Lu.

438
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:47,080
You guys decide who goes

439
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:47,440
first.

440
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:48,200
Rock, paper, scissors.

441
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:50,580
(Lu Yanting decides the order.)

442
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,240
We go first.

443
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,240
No, he won, so he chooses.

444
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:55,540
(Driven by competition)

445
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:56,520
Then you go first.

446
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,620
(It's all yours, bro)

447
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,040
Can't wait any longer.

448
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,640
Keep going.

449
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,380
(Only five seconds left...)

450
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,280
Does that count?

451
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:05,720
No.

452
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,200
Alright.

453
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,080
Put me down.

454
00:12:08,700 --> 00:12:11,620
(Fashion guru)

455
00:12:11,820 --> 00:12:13,420
(Scoring the third group)

456
00:12:13,580 --> 00:12:15,180
(T-shirt incomplete, not counted)

457
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:17,860
(1 point)

458
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:20,020
(High-score shirts coming!)

459
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,360
One, two...

460
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:24,720
Three, four, five, six, seven, eight.

461
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,000
Extra one for you.

462
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,660
(All buttons fastened)

463
00:12:27,660 --> 00:12:28,460
(T-shirt: 1 point, Shirt: 5 points)

464
00:12:28,460 --> 00:12:29,560
That's pretty good.

465
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,260
(Serious, focused)

466
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:32,320
One, two,

467
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:34,160
three, four, five, six, seven.

468
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:35,780
(T-shirt: 1 point, Shirt: 10 points)

469
00:12:36,380 --> 00:12:39,100
(Zhao Enda & Yang Tinghong: 1 T-shirt,
2 shirts, 11 points, currently 1st place)

470
00:12:39,180 --> 00:12:41,620
(Currently the highest score: 11 pts)

471
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,480
We'll definitely be pumped up.

472
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:44,600
We will?

473
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,040
Yeah.

474
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,640
Yeah, we love it.

475
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,540
(We know each other so well.)

476
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:49,520
Got this in the bag.

477
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:50,300
(Confidently)

478
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,600
Got this in the bag.

479
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,360
Got this in the bag?

480
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:53,080
(So confident?)

481
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:53,680
Just kidding.

482
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:56,720
I'm glad we got 11 points.

483
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:57,960
(Confidence +1)
That's it.

484
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,840
(Confident smile)

485
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,280
Let's go.

486
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:04,220
(Round 4 begins)

487
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:08,020
(Burst out laughing)

488
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:09,240
Hurry!

489
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:12,620
(Successfully put on)

490
00:13:12,660 --> 00:13:13,860
(First T-shirt done)

491
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:14,940
(Excitement takes over.)

492
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,640
We'll definitely be pumped up.

493
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:18,740
("Prophecy" confirmed)

494
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:19,920
Hurry!

495
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,340
(Laughing while finishing the second one)

496
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:29,600
(Concerned)
Are you tired? You're shaking.

497
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,880
It's from holding this position.

498
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,640
I told you not to bend too much.

499
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:34,920
Yeah, don't bend too much.

500
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:36,040
You're totally right.

501
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:37,520
That's hilarious.

502
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:40,620
(How to keep a straight face)

503
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:41,520
Hurry!

504
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:47,560
That's a sleeve,

505
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,400
